============================================================
PHASE 11 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the AI operations, governance, and compliance control plane for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Add AI model registry
2. Add prompt template registry
3. Add prompt versioning
4. Add AI request tracing
5. Add AI cost estimation
6. Add AI provider routing policy
7. Add AI evaluation test suites
8. Add golden dataset evaluation
9. Add red-team simulation framework
10. Add governance policy engine
11. Add compliance rules and evidence collection
12. Add data retention policy system
13. Add DLP scanner for secrets and sensitive data
14. Add marketplace plugin review workflow
15. Add security review pipeline for plugins and prompts
16. Add approval workflow engine
17. Add governance dashboard pages
18. Add AI Ops dashboard pages
19. Add compliance report generator
20. Add tests for governance, AI Ops, policy enforcement, and review workflows

IMPORTANT SAFETY RULES:
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- Do not bypass billing entitlement checks.
- Do not expose secrets in prompts, traces, logs, exports, reports, or frontend.
- AI providers must be replaceable.
- Mock AI Ops must work without external API keys.
- Governance policies must fail closed in production.
- Plugin review must block unsafe plugins by default.
- Red-team framework must be defensive and validation-only.
- Compliance evidence must not contain raw secrets.

