============================================================
MODEL REGISTRY REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/aiops/model_registry.py

Methods:

- register_model(record)
- list_models(organization_id, workspace_id)
- get_model(model_id)
- update_model(model_id, patch)
- disable_model(model_id)
- select_default_model(provider=None, capability=None)

Rules:
- Tenant scoped.
- Mock model must be registered by default.
- Claude model shell may be registered if configured.
- Disabled model cannot be used.
- Deprecated model emits warning.
- No API keys are stored in model registry.

============================================================
PROMPT REGISTRY REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/aiops/prompt_registry.py

Methods:

- create_prompt(request)
- create_version(prompt_id, template_text, variables, change_notes)
- list_prompts(status=None)
- get_prompt(prompt_id)
- get_version(version_id)
- submit_for_review(prompt_id)
- approve_version(version_id, approved_by)
- reject_version(version_id, reason)
- deprecate_prompt(prompt_id)
- rollback_to_version(prompt_id, version_id)

Rules:
- Tenant scoped.
- Prompt variables must be explicit.
- Approved version required for production usage.
- Draft prompts allowed in development only.
- Every version change audited.
- DLP scan must run before approval.
- Rejected prompts cannot be rendered for production use.

============================================================
PROMPT RENDERER REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/aiops/prompt_renderer.py

Methods:

- render(prompt_id, variables, require_approved=True) -> RenderedPrompt
- estimate_tokens(text) -> int
- validate_variables(prompt_version, variables)
- redact_sensitive_values(text)

Rules:
- Missing variables must raise clean error.
- Extra variables allowed but ignored or recorded.
- Rendered prompt length must respect PROMPT_RENDER_MAX_LENGTH.
- DLP scanner must run on rendered text.
- Secrets must be redacted in traces.

============================================================
PROVIDER ROUTER REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/aiops/provider_router.py

Methods:

- choose_provider(request_type, capability, organization_id, workspace_id)
- route_request(prompt, model_preference=None, fallback=True)
- record_provider_failure(provider, error)
- get_provider_status()

Rules:
- Mock provider always available.
- External providers require config.
- If provider unavailable, fallback to mock in development.
- In production with AIOPS_FAIL_CLOSED=true, block unsafe provider fallback for sensitive actions.
- Provider decisions must be traced.

============================================================
AI TRACE AND COST REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/aiops/ai_trace_service.py

Methods:

- record_trace(...)
- list_traces(filters)
- get_trace(trace_id)
- redact_trace(trace)

Create:

backend/app/aiops/cost_service.py

Methods:

- estimate_cost(provider, model_name, token_input, token_output)
- summarize_costs(organization_id, workspace_id, range)
- get_cost_by_provider()
- get_cost_by_feature()

Rules:
- Never store raw secrets in traces.
- Store input/output summaries, not full sensitive payloads by default.
- Cost estimation works with mock values.
- Cost summary must be tenant-scoped.

============================================================
EVALUATION SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/aiops/eval_datasets.py
backend/app/aiops/eval_runner.py

Default evaluation suites:

1. agent_message_quality
- CEO → Janie response quality
- No secret leakage
- Clear operational summary

2. trading_analysis_safety
- Trading response includes dry-run / educational wording
- Does not claim guaranteed profit
- Does not bypass Guardian

3. content_policy_quality
- Social content includes required disclaimer when trading-related
- Blocks misleading claims

4. plugin_safety_quality
- Plugin result cannot request secrets
- Plugin result cannot invoke live actions

Eval runner methods:

- create_dataset()
- list_datasets()
- run_eval(prompt_id, version_id, model_id, dataset_id)
- get_eval_run(run_id)
- list_eval_runs()

Scoring:
- pass/fail assertions
- score 0–100
- failed case details
- warning notes

Rules:
- Max cases capped by EVALS_MAX_CASES_PER_RUN.
- Eval failures do not crash system.
- Results are tenant-scoped.
- Eval run events emitted.

============================================================
RED-TEAM SIMULATION REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/aiops/redteam.py

Purpose:
Defensive validation only.

Methods:

- run_prompt_redteam(prompt_id, version_id)
- run_plugin_redteam(plugin_id)
- run_content_policy_redteam()
- list_redteam_runs()
- get_redteam_run(run_id)

Scenarios:
- secret leakage attempt detection
- prompt injection resistance check
- policy bypass request check
- plugin unsafe action check
- guaranteed-profit language check
- unauthorized tenant access check

Rules:
- Do not generate harmful instructions.
- Use safe abstract test strings.
- Do not include real credentials.
- Results should classify:
  - blocked
  - warning
  - failed
  - passed
- Red-team runs are dry-run by default.

